race.comment: Keen to be with SUNSETS (1) second up. He was having his first run for the Bedggood yard at Caulfield Heath and ran far better than his $41 starting price would've suggested, getting into third late behind two smart types. He'd lost his way a bit but remember he'd run third to Riff Rocket in a G1 Victoria Derby. Fitter now, suited to 1700m and looks a good price. UNSEEN RULER (7) has been good in two runs back from a spell, not far away in a similar race here as favourite last time out. Drawn to get back again but should be hard to hold out. MISTER ME (6) finished just ahead of UNSEEN RULER there and has to have claims especially with his favourable pattern. CHAIRMAN (9) is going well in these sorts of country cups and has claims again. BRUNG KING (2) won well in easier last time and is in the mix.
